<h3>Best Places to Ski in January</h3>
<p data-pm-slice="1 1 []">January is generally one of the quietest months in ski resorts, so there won't be as many other people on the slopes. This means you can do as many runs in a day as you wish and you won't have to wait long for a lift either. And if you're looking for advanced terrain, there should be fresh powder to carve some first tracks in.</p>
